We have two Rev Blinkin LED controllers driving 5V LED strips. On several occasions they have randomly switched from the 5V output to the 12V output shutting off our LED strips. We thought they might be browning out but a couple of times the robot has been stationary. Anyone experienced this behavior and know the root cause?

Rev Blinkin Resetting Strip Mode Randomly Technical Discussion
We have a Rev Blinkin that works say 90% of the time. The 10% is that it resets the strip mode to the 5v strip randomly. We’re using the 12v mode to show cube/cone mode for our intake. There’s no chance anything is hitting the button while running and you seemingly can’t set the strip mode over pwm. Has anyone else encountered a similar issue? The 12V is plugged into the pdp but the lights have never turned off in correlation with any specific event like a brownout or a hard hit etc. Could it b…
